JAPANESE OAT CRISPS Makes 36 biscuits.Ingredients:200g butter300g (1 cups) sugar100g (1 cup) rolled oats240g (2 cups) cake flour5ml (1 tsp) bicarbonate of soda1 extra-large egg, lightly beatenMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) Melt the butter in a saucepan. Combine the sugar, oats, flour and bicarbonate of soda in a mixing bowl. Beat in the egg and melted butter.3) Roll the dough into walnut-sized balls and place on a greased or sprayed baking tray, leaving space between for them to spread. Flatten each ball slightly and bake for 10-15 minutes until golden and crisp. Cool on the tray. COCONUT KRISPIES Makes 70Gooey St Louis: a new take on cheese cakeIngredients:250g butter200-300g (1-1 cups) white sugar2 extra-large eggs5ml (1 tsp) vanilla essence50ml peanut butter240g (2 cups) cake flour5ml (1 tsp) baking powderPinch of salt5ml (1 tsp) bicarbonate of soda160g (2 cups) desiccated coconut200g (2 cups) rolled oats500ml (2 cups) Rice KrispiesMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla essence and peanut butter.3) In a separate bowl, sift the flour, baking powder, salt and bicarbonate of soda together, then beat into the creamed mixture. Fold in the coconut, oats and Rice Krispies.4) Place teaspoonfuls of the mixture on greased or sprayed baking trays and flatten slightly with a fork. Bake for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on trays, then transfer to a wire rack. HEALTH BISCUITS Makes 50-60Ingredients:160g butter, softened100g ( cup) white sugar100g ( cup) brown sugar2.5ml ( tsp) bicarbonate of soda2.5ml ( tsp) ground cinnamon1 extra-large egg125ml ( cup) sunflower oil60ml ( cup) runny honey5ml (1 tsp) vanilla essence150g (1 cups) cake flour125ml ( cup) wheat germ, or a mixture of sunflower, sesame and flax seeds250g (2 cups) rolled oatsMethod:1) Preheat the oven to t 180 C.2) In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds. Add the white and brown sugar, bicarbonate of soda and cinnamon and beat until combined. Beat in the egg, oil, honey and vanilla until combined. Beat in flour and wheat germ (or seeds) and then stir in rolled oats with a wooden spoon.3) Place large spoonfuls of the mixture on sprayed or greased baking trays and flatten slightly. Bake for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on trays for 2-3 minutes then transfer to wire racks to cool completely.